    h2 Universal Logic Gates
    p.
        AND, OR and NOT gates can be connected together to realize any logic function. It is possible to use only one 
        type of gate for this purpose so that one needs to procure only one type of gate for this design. And more 
        importantly, fabrication of Integrated Circuit that performs a logic operation becomes easier when gate of 
        only one kind is used. Gates, which can perform this task, are called Universal logic gates. Clearly, basic 
        gates like AND, OR and NOT don’t fit into this category for the simple reason that conversion among themselves 
        itself are not possible. As for example, one cannot get OR operation by using any number or combination of AND 
        gates.
    h3 1.) The NAND Gate (NOT AND)
    p.
        It is a logic circuit in which AND gate is followed by a NOT gate. The output of NAND gate is high if any of 
        the inputs are low. Its symbol is an AND gate with a small circle on the output. Fig-12 shows the symbol of 
        2-input NAND gate. The small circle represents inversion. Boolean expression for NAND gate is as follows:
    p $$ Y = \neg{(AB)}$$
    img(src='/public/images/elec-comm/01/lab02/nand-gate-schema.png')
    p.center Fig.-12: Symbol of 2-input NAND gate
    br
    include gatetables/nandgate-quad.pug 
    br
