    p An NAND gate can have as many inputs as desired. No matter how many inputs, the action of any NAND gate is summarized like this:
    p <strong> All high inputs produce a low output. </strong>
    p The logic symbol of a three input NAND gate is shown in Fig-13.
    img(src='/public/images/elec-comm/01/lab02/nandgate-3in-schema.png')
    p.center Fig.-13: Symbol of 3-input NAND gate
