    p An NOR gate can have as many inputs as desired. No matter how many inputs, the action of any NOR gate is summarized like this:
    p <strong> All low inputs produce a high output. </strong>
    p The logic symbol of a three inputs NOR gate is shown in Fig-18.
    img(src='/public/images/elec-comm/01/lab02/norgate-3in-schema.png')
    p.center Fig.-18: Symbol of 3-input NOR gate
    br
    include gatetables/norgate-triple.pug 
    br
    p.center Table 8: Truth table for 3-input NOR gate
    p IC 7402 and IC 7427 are standard TTL ICs of 2 input and 3input NOR gate respectively
    h3 2-INPUT NOR GATE IC-7402
    p IC-7402 (Fig-19) is a device containing four independent gates each of which performs the logic NOR function. Pins 14 and 7 provide power for all four logic gates.
    h3 3-INPUT NOR GATE IC-7427
    p IC-7427 (Fig-20) is a Triple 3-input NOR gate and contains three independent gates each of which performs logic NOR operation
    .row 
        .column 
